==Translingual==
===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} [[ξίφος]] (''xiphos'') "[[sword]]" and [[ουρά]] (''oura'') "[[tail]]", in reference to the long, slender, stiff tail of the horseshoe crab.
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Xiphosura'''

#{{zoology}}: An [[order]] of the class [[Merostomata]] distinguished from all other [[chelicerate]]s by having [[compound eye]]s.  The only living [[xiphosuran]]s are the [[horseshoe crab]]s.

